Interface Named

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    MutableNamed
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractNamed, NameResolver, NameResolverFactory

    public interface Named
extends Serializable
    An owner of Names that can retrieve them efficiently when asked for them by NameType.
    Author:
    Laird Nelson
    See Also:
    getName(NameType), Name

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      Name getName(NameType nameType)
      Retrieves a Name that belongs to this Named that is appropriate for the supplied NameType, or null if no such Name can be found.

    • Method Detail

      • getName

        Name getName(NameType nameType)
        Retrieves a Name that belongs to this Named that is appropriate for the supplied NameType, or null if no such Name can be found.

        Implementations of this method are permitted to return null.

        Parameters:
        nameType - the NameType for which a Name will be sought; may be null in which case the implementation may decide what kind of Name to return (including null)
        Returns:
        a Name indexed under the supplied NameType, or null
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if nameType is not accepted by the implementation of this method for any reason
